snippet.textDisplay:
Love from Bangladesh. Beautiful song,lyrics and rhythm. Didnt understand a single word, but kept listening on loop. Sometimes it become difficult to understand normal Urdu,but these are just on another level. Translation helps to understand the meaning but not the lyrics, what words they are saying etc. 
Phir milenge from coke studio 14 is a best example of lyrics+ translation. In the CC we can actually read what young stunners were rapping otherwise it was impossible to understand.

Taweel hay gham ki sham, kahani mohabbat ki mukhtasir. 😢

snippet.textDisplay:
Most people do not understand the story behind this Song
So here is the short story, the story of Maanu(male singer) is starting to fall in love with Annural(female singer), but a jealous third person in the club wants Annural for himself. The third person realizes that Maanu has given Annural a red scarf, and he takes the scarf and puts it in the vanity room to make Annural think that she cheated on him. The other woman in the club sees what the third person has done, and she tells Annural. Annural runs out to try and clarify the situation with Maanu, but the ending shows that he throws the scarf away and goes back on the train, and she misses him.
